{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieved textual subgraphs are transformed into hierarchical text descriptions by our proposed graph algorithms to form hard prompts, which encode the topological information in texts.",
    "Soft prompts are generated by encoding the graph's topological information directly via graph encoders, encoding text information as node/edge attributes in graphs.",
    "Finally, the generation process is guided by both hard and soft prompts for LLM to gain a deeper understanding of the relationships between entities, leading to responses that are well-aligned with the underlying textual graph context.",
    "Empirical results on multi-hop graph reasoning tasks demonstrate that our GRAG approach significantly outperforms RAG-based retrievers and LLM baselines in graph reasoning scenarios.",
    "In particular, Frozen LLM with GRAG outperforms fine-tuned LLM on all tasks."
  ]
}